title: My phone is connected to a Wi-Fi network but I cannot open web pages. Why?
answer:
Possible causes are as follows: 


 l xDSL connections fail if the hotspot, for example, a wireless router, uses xDSL to access the Internet. 

 l Domain name service fails if you can use QQ but cannot open webpages. 

Access restrictions are set on the Wi-Fi hotspot
